{"recommendationid": "14855265", "author": {"steamid": "76561198090898380", "num_games_owned": 0, "num_reviews": 2, "playtime_forever": 687, "playtime_last_two_weeks": 0, "playtime_at_review": 599, "last_played": 1440803339}, "language": "english", "review": "Overall this is a pretty great game. Yes the "cannon" mission is pretty short but the side missions and multiple other objectives in the game definately make it a fair value in my opinion. It is definately just a taste of the full MGS V game and makes you really want the actual Phantom Pain to drop. 

Overall this is a decent PC port. Interacting with some of the menus is really janky if you are using a mouse and Keyboard, and the controls for these can't be set in the options menu. Overall I'd give the game a B. It is great getting you ready for MGS V: TPP, but if you are not interested in completeing the different achievements in the game there probably isn't enough value to justify the price-tag. 

TL:DR - Short, but a great game for metal gear fans and people who like challenging achievements.", "timestamp_created": 1426190261, "timestamp_updated": 1426190261, "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "weighted_vote_score": 0.5, "comment_count": 0, "steam_purchase": true, "received_for_free": false, "written_during_early_access": false, "primarily_steam_deck": false}

{"recommendationid": "14847235", "author": {"steamid": "76561197960923943", "num_games_owned": 0, "num_reviews": 11, "playtime_forever": 179, "playtime_last_two_weeks": 0, "playtime_at_review": 179, "last_played": 1425879958}, "language": "english", "review": "Metal Gear Appetizer.

