{"recommendationid": "14639423", "author": {"steamid": "76561198141733817", "num_games_owned": 391, "num_reviews": 46, "playtime_forever": 1043, "playtime_last_two_weeks": 0, "playtime_at_review": 1040, "last_played": 1441426762}, "language": "english", "review": "Worth playing but don't try to pay very much for it as it feels quite incomplete.  The mechanics are quite good, Kiefer Sutherland does a fine bit of work though I see no reason for the change, and the main mission and the Deja Vu mission are laden with Kojima's style.  My only complaint is that it feels like a handful of VR missions and a demo (the main mission stands out as the main mission, however it does that; just seems more effort was put into it).  All the missions are good.  The game is gorgeous as well, if you care about that type of thing.

My only complaints are the length of the main mission, the odd function that you're apparently invisible once you're crawling (I've crawled past guards' feet essentially as close as I could be without touching them and they didn't seem to mind), and that it doesn't feel like the 1970s with all that iDroid stuff.  The only proper complaint is the length however.

