{"recommendationid": "14328224", "author": {"steamid": "76561198055359967", "num_games_owned": 839, "num_reviews": 48, "playtime_forever": 2104, "playtime_last_two_weeks": 0, "playtime_at_review": 347, "last_played": 1706250273}, "language": "english", "review": "This game can be short if thats just the way you want to see it. But there is MUCH more to this game than a lot of people give it credit for. 

The Fox Engine is clearly a great looking and optimized engine that works on all platforms. The level of detail possible is really something else. This is all done while the game runs extremely well, and hardly any hicups even when the Graphic settings are pushed to the max. 

The action feels tense and can have a great deal of difficulty. This all the more adds to the stealth of the game, trying to avoid conflicts, as they can be difficult to escape. This game has shown me that the Phantom Pain will be a damn good game, and I cant wait to get my paws on it.", "timestamp_created": 1423075847, "timestamp_updated": 1423075847, "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 1, "votes_funny": 0, "weighted_vote_score": "0.522727251052856445", "comment_count": 0, "steam_purchase": true, "received_for_free": false, "written_during_early_access": false, "primarily_steam_deck": false}

