{"recommendationid": "14029324", "author": {"steamid": "76561198008784652", "num_games_owned": 1113, "num_reviews": 59, "playtime_forever": 405, "playtime_last_two_weeks": 0, "playtime_at_review": 364, "last_played": 1441829522}, "language": "english", "review": "[h1][b]Jack Bauer and Travis Touchdown on a white-knuckle mission to save George from summer camp.[/b][/h1]

Amazing port and great introduction to the world of MGS:V at a price much easier to stomach than the original console release.

Here's hoping the full game offers more of this in spades.", "timestamp_created": 1421498220, "timestamp_updated": 1421498220, "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 16, "votes_funny": 25, "weighted_vote_score": "0.522620022296905518", "comment_count": 1, "steam_purchase": true, "received_for_free": false, "written_during_early_access": false, "primarily_steam_deck": false}

{"recommendationid": "13991984", "author": {"steamid": "76561198098806886", "num_games_owned": 0, "num_reviews": 10, "playtime_forever": 1109, "playtime_last_two_weeks": 0, "playtime_at_review": 678, "last_played": 1716434355}, "language": "english", "review": "Best game available on Steam in 2014. I've a big fan of the original MGS games which all shared the spotlight of the first ps1 game. I was hoping this new storyline would go back to the first games' sucesses, and time period... and it does, all the while adding the right amount of game mechanics from the current generation of games. This game does similar things like FarCry4 in which you can mark enemies to give you awareness of your surroundings, but in this game you also have the third person view which makes sneaking around so much easier. Its clear that the designers focused a lot on making the controls more intuitive. In tense firefights the controls flow seemlessly never taking you out of the action. 

But if youve never played MGS, the crowning achievement for the franchise is sound. Realistic weapons having realistic sounds in different environments emerses you into the role of being a one man army. This new MGS delivers that in a big way. The sound and music puts you into the game better than any game ive ever played.

My favorite part of the game though has to be the side missions. I enjoyed the old VR mission game based of sons of liberty so I was happy to see they included those. All in all this game is worth every penny. 10/10", "timestamp_created": 1421305465, "timestamp_updated": 1421305465, "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "weighted_vote_score": 0.5, "comment_count": 0, "steam_purchase": true, "received_for_free": false, "written_during_early_access": false, "primarily_steam_deck": false}

{"recommendationid": "13991576", "author": {"steamid": "76561198001221200", "num_games_owned": 1350, "num_reviews": 179, "playtime_forever": 610, "playtime_last_two_weeks": 0, "playtime_at_review": 317, "last_played": 1443683202}, "language": "english", "review": "Metal Gear Solid V: Ground Zeroes is a short but good entry of the MGS series. The gameplay itself is like that of it's predecessors, not counting Revengeance, but it gives players some twist such as marking enemies, finding alternative routes to an objective (such as hiding in a truck, crawling in a vent, or just sneaking through the door) and looking beautiful even on low settings. 

The game does suffer some flaws. For one, it's short. The campaign itself is just a prologue for the upcoming Phantom Pain so it's just one mission, not counting the pseudo-historical missions. Another flaw (though subjective) is the fact that the checkpoint system can be abused to refill tranquilizer ammo for those that want to be the technical pacifist (I say technical since you might just end up knocking out the enemies via CQC.) though it is at least evened by penalizing players in subtracting their ranking score.

Overall, Ground Zeroes is an entry of the series that is worth playing, especially for those on PC who either want to play a Metal Gear Solid Game and/or those who want to play a game that emphasizes the importance of stealth.", "timestamp_created": 1421301258, "timestamp_updated": 1421301258, "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "weighted_vote_score": 0.5, "comment_count": 0, "steam_purchase": true, "received_for_free": false, "written_during_early_access": false, "primarily_steam_deck": false}

{"recommendationid": "13989886", "author": {"steamid": "76561197989270364", "num_games_owned": 505, "num_reviews": 64, "playtime_forever": 1096, "playtime_last_two_weeks": 0, "playtime_at_review": 274, "last_played": 1441084917}, "language": "english", "review": "Mostly excellent PC version of a great game. My only complaint would be that the menus can't be navigated by mouse, but that's easy to get used to. Haven't encountered any other issues in that regard. I guess reflex mode probably makes the game a lot easier than was intended now that you can use a mouse, but you can always turn that off.

As for the game itself, some will complain that it's a demo and well... It basically is, but there's enough content here with enough replay value to merit paying over $10. The controls are very in-depth, the mechanics are top-notch (apart from the sometimes wonky marking mechanic,) the gameplay is very open-ended. There is one side mission that kind of sucks but if this game is any indication, The Phantom Pain will be one of the best MGS games. And that means a lot

It's not really essential to buy right now since I'm sure it'll be included in some kind of deal with The Phantom Pain, but if you're a fan who wants to preview the game and make the most of Ground Zeroes, I highly recommend grabbing it beforehand.", "timestamp_created": 1421287279, "timestamp_updated": 1421287279, "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 1, "votes_funny": 0, "weighted_vote_score": "0.512687444686889648", "comment_count": 0, "steam_purchase": true, "received_for_free": false, "written_during_early_access": false, "primarily_steam_deck": false}

{"recommendationid": "13942668", "author": {"steamid": "76561198025617084", "num_games_owned": 0, "num_reviews": 36, "playtime_forever": 487, "playtime_last_two_weeks": 0, "playtime_at_review": 49, "last_played": 1680267183}, "language": "english", "review": "I wont lie, this is just a demo, but it's a really fun, really well made demo. Runs smooth, looks great. Snake's rear end isn't the main star either. 

It looks as if they toned down the well formed curves on the butt we all grew to know and love, but it takes away very little from the over all demo. 

5/5 I like the new buttless direction we seem to be going in.", "timestamp_created": 1420986875, "timestamp_updated": 1420986875, "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "weighted_vote_score": 0.5, "comment_count": 0, "steam_purchase": true, "received_for_free": false, "written_during_early_access": false, "primarily_steam_deck": false}

{"recommendationid": "13920177", "author": {"steamid": "76561198092319522", "num_games_owned": 0, "num_reviews": 20, "playtime_forever": 137, "playtime_last_two_weeks": 0, "playtime_at_review": 137, "last_played": 1420871984}, "language": "english", "review": "It costs you a dollar a minute to play this game/Demo. That is how long you will play it. 20 minutes, not including cut scenes. 

