{"recommendationid": "13451686", "author": {"steamid": "76561197969648577", "num_games_owned": 630, "num_reviews": 26, "playtime_forever": 806, "playtime_last_two_weeks": 0, "playtime_at_review": 113, "last_played": 1441079908}, "language": "english", "review": "GROUND ZEROES is a fantastic achievement from Kojima Productions, not just in regards to its excellent world buliding, game mechanics and storytelling, but also with respect to the excellent PC release.  Regarding the game itself, it's excellent albeit brief.  If the idea of replaying missions to try alternate strategies or to beat your score, it's probably best to hold off for the main dish when PHANTOM PAIN is released next year.  If you enjoy replaying missions, self-improvement and pushing at the seams of open world gameplay, then GROUND ZEROES is an absolute must-play. The only point of contention I experienced in my first play-through of the main mission – which took around 80 minutes, but I plan on doing it at least 3 or 4 more times, not to mention the 6 or so side missions you can unlock – were some aspects of the storytelling. I won't go into it too much here, but there's reason for healthy discussion on the game's treatment of its sole female character.

The PC version of the game is rock solid.  I'm not sure why they released the minimum requirements they did; I'm a mix of above and below and the game ran at nearly 60FPS at 900P (2013 rMBP w/GeForce 750m, 16GB RAM, Core i7 2.3GHz). Controls are excellent and the game has a healthy selection of graphics options.

Overall I can see myself returning to this small but exquisitely crafted game many, many times.  It's a ton of fun and easily the best controlling Metal Gear Solid ever released. I don't regret splittling with $15 for the experience and I simply can't wait until I get my hands on THE PHANTOM PAIN next year (Note to the developers: *please* release the PC version at the same time as the consoles).", "timestamp_created": 1419004943, "timestamp_updated": 1419004943, "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "weighted_vote_score": 0.5, "comment_count": 0, "steam_purchase": true, "received_for_free": false, "written_during_early_access": false, "primarily_steam_deck": false}

{"recommendationid": "13451398", "author": {"steamid": "76561197961980776", "num_games_owned": 867, "num_reviews": 29, "playtime_forever": 324, "playtime_last_two_weeks": 0, "playtime_at_review": 164, "last_played": 1440769520}, "language": "english", "review": "Let's get the popular opinion out of the way first, the game is shorter than the old MGS1 demo from demo disk in a PC Gamer magazine. Pretty disappointing, seriously. Dropped the ball hard.

